Quote: Two types of gecko are also found in the Mackenzie Basin. The Southern Alps gecko (,i>Hoplodactylus aff. maculatus 'Southern Alps'</i>) lives near rocky outcrops, screes, boulder banks and rock tumbles. The jewelled gecko (<i>Naultinus gemmeus</i>) lives in forest and shrubland.
Notes: http://doc.org.nz/publications/getting-involved/students-and-teachers/themes/river-life/lizards/

