Quote: Most specimens of Southern Alps gecko are readilydistinguished by the combination of small adult size(i.e. 53-60 mm SVL) and a short, tapering distalphalange. In addition, the markings tend to be verydrab, and often include pinkish tones.
Notes: http://www.doc.govt.nz/upload/documents/science-and-technical/otagogeckosa.pdf
